.TH dce_config 8dce
.iX "\*Ldce_config\*O command"
.iX "installing DCE" "start up command"
.iX "configuring DCE" "start up command"
.SH "NAME"
.PP
\*Ldce_config\*O - Installs, configures, and starts up DCE 
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sS
\*Ldce_config\*O [\*L-i\*O] [\*L-e \*Venvironment_file\*O] [\*L-c \*Vcommand_file\*O]
.sE
.SH "OPTIONS"
.VL .5ii
.LI "\*L-i\*O"
The \%\*L-i\*O option tells \*Ldce_config\*O to look in the \*L/etc\*O 
directory of the install area (which is generally \*L/opt/dce1.0/etc\*O) 
for the component scripts it needs to run.  
After you have invoked \*Ldce_config\*O once with the \*L-i\*O 
option, you do not need to use the option again.
.LI "\*L-e\*O \*Venvironment_file\*O"
The \%\*L-e\*O option causes \*Ldce_config\*O to source \*Venvironment_file\*O 
at startup.  The \*Venvironment_file\*O variable represents
a user-created file that sets the DCE and Distributed File Service (DFS)
variables that specfy responses to the \*Ldce_config\*O user prompts.  
Note that if you do not specify the \%\*L-e\*O option, \*Ldce_config\*O 
looks for the \*L/etc/dce_config.conf\*O file and sources it if it 
exists.  If the file does not exist, 
it uses shell variable 
settings if they are set.
.LI "\*L-c\*O \*Vcommand_file\*O"
The \%\*L-c\*O option causes \*Ldce_config\*O to source \*Vcommand_file\*O 
at startup.  The \*Vcommand_file\*O variable
represents a user-created shell script that 
initiates installation and configuration processing.
.LE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
The \*Ldce_config\*O shell command invokes a menu-driven interface that 
installs, configures, and starts up DCE.  The \*Ldce_config\*O command
displays a hierarchy of menus and invokes individual installation and configuration
routines, according to users' menu selections. 
.PP 
Installation routines store the binaries required for the server installation
that is selected into \*L$DCELOCAL\*O.  Binaries required for a client
installation are stored on every machine.  The configuration menu consists
of initial cell configuration, additional server configuration, and DCE
client configuration.  The security server and the first Cell Directory
Service (CDS) server
constitute initial cell configuration.  
...\" .zA "enh,9287,add new options"  
.PP
.ne 2
If you specify an environment file with the \%\*L-e\*O option and a command 
file with the \%\*L-c\*O option,  
you can completely automate 
\*Ldce_config\*O processing.
.nL
.SS "The Command File" 
The command file consists of \*Linstall\*O and \*Lconfig\*O command lines 
that specify the component to install and, 
for DFS, the type of server. 
.PP
A sample command file, \*Lconfig.cmd\*O, is provided by 
OSF with the DCE source.  You can copy the file and use it 
as supplied or you can use it as guide to 
creating your own environment file.  
The sample file 
is not copied to the 
install tree during DCE installation. 
.PP
The \*Linstall\*O lines are in the following form:
.iS
install \*Vcomponent\*O [\*Vdfs_server\*O]
.iE
where:
.VL 1i
.LI "\*Vcomponent\*O" 
Can be one of the following values:
.VL 1i
.LI "\*Lsec\*O"
Master security server binaries    
.LI "\*Lcds\*O"
Initial CDS server binaries 
.LI "\*Lgds\*O"
GDS server binaries
.LI "\*Ldts\*O"
Distributed Time Service (DTS) server binaries  
.LI "\*Lclient\*O"
DCE client binaries 
.LI "\*Lsec-replica\*O"
Security replica binaries
.LI "\*Lappdev\*O"
Interface Definition Language (IDL) compiler 
and header files for use in DCE application development
.LI "\*Lcdsbrowser\*O"
CDS browser utility
.LI "\*Lnidl_to_idl\*O"
A utility to convert files written in NIDL to files written in IDL
.LE
.LI "\*Vdfs_server\*O" 
Specifies the type of DFS server to install; can be
one of the following values:
.VL 1i
.LI "\*Lclient\*O"
DFS client
.LI "\*Lscm\*O"
System control machine
.LI "\*Lprivatefs\*O"
Private file server
.LI "\*Lfs\*O"
File server
.LI "\*Lfldb\*O"
File location database server
.LE
.LE
.nL
.ne 11
The \*Lconfig\*O lines are in the following form:
.iS
config \*Vcomponent\*L 
            {
             client | 
             gda | 
             sec {client | server | replica} | 
             cds {client | server | replica} | 
             dts {clerk | local | global | ntp-provider | null-provider}             
             dfs {client | scm | privatefs | fs | fldb}
             }
.iE
where:
.VL 1i
.LI "\*Vcomponent\*O" 
Can be one of the following values:
.VL .75i
.LI "\*Lclient\*O"
DCE client configuration 
.LI "\*Lgda\*O"
GDA configuration 
.LI "\*Lsec\*O"
Security configuration of any one of the following:
.VL .75i
.LI "\*Lclient\*O"
Security client machine
.LI "\*Lserver\*O"
Security master server machine
.LI "\*Lreplica\*O"
Security replica machine
.LE
.LI "\*Lcds\*O"
CDS configuration of any one of the following:
.VL .75i
.LI "\*Lclient\*O"
CDS client machine
.LI "\*Lserver\*O"
CDS initial server machine
.LI "\*Lreplica\*O"
Additional CDS server machines
.LE
.LI "\*Ldts\*O"
DTS configuration of any one of the following:
.VL .75i
.LI "\*Lclerk\*O"
DTS clerk machine
.LI "\*Llocal\*O"
DTS local server machine
.LI "\*Lglobal\*O"
DTS global server machine
.LI "\*Lntp-provider\*O"
DTS NTP time-provider machine
.nL
.ne 2
.LI "\*Lnull-provider\*O"
DTS null time-provider
.LE 
.nL
.ne 5
.LI "\*Ldfs\*O"
DFS configuration of any one of the following:
.VL .75i
.LI "\*Lclient\*O"
DFS client specify
.LI "\*Lscm\*O"
System control machine
.LI "\*Lprivatefs\*O"
Private file server machine
.LI "\*Lfs\*O"
File server machine
.LI "\*Lfldb\*O"
File location database server machine
.LE
.LE
.LE
.SS "The Environment File"
The environment file sets the DCE and DFS variables.  
The file entries are in the following form:
.iS
\*Vvariable\*L=\*Vvalue\*O
.iE
To change a value, simply replace it with the new 
value. 
.PP
A sample environment file, \*Lconfig.env\*O, is provided by 
OSF with the DCE source.  You can copy the file and use it 
as supplied or you can use it as guide to 
creating your own environment file.  The sample file is not copied to the 
install tree during DCE installation.  
.PP
.SS "The DCE and DFS Variables"
The first of the tables that follows lists the 
DCE variables you can set for \*Ldce_config\*O processing. 
The second of the tables lists the DFS variables you can set.  
In the tables, the term default refers 
to the setting assigned to the variable by OSF. 
.PP
.ps 11
.vs 12
...\" 
...\" lB | lBw(3.3i)
...\" lb | lw(3.3i).
...\" 
