Indication of whether or not to synchronize all client clocks with 
the security server clock;  \*Ly\*O indicates that client and server 
clocks will be synchronized while \*Ln\*O indicates they will not.  
If set to \*Ln\*O, and clocks are out of sync by more than value
specified in the \*LTOLERANCE_SEC\*O variable, user is prompted whether 
or not to synchronize them. Valid only if \*LCHECK_TIME\*O variable  
is set to \*Ly\*O. For DFS machine configurations, should be set to \*Ly\*O.
T}
_
TIME_SERVER@T{
.iX "TIME_SERVER dce_config environment variable"
Specifies host that security client will try
to synchronize its clock against. Host must have a DTS server
(\*Ldtsd\*O) running. Recommended choice for host is the one
running the master security server (name specified
in the \*LSEC_SERVER\*O variable).
T}
